{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 23,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Chronicles 23 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:1",
      "text": "When David was old and full of days, he made Solomon his son king over Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:2",
      "text": "David assembled all the leaders of Israel and the priests and the Levites.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:3",
      "text": "The Levites, thirty years old and upward, were numbered, and the total was thirty-eight thousand men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:4",
      "text": "“Twenty-four thousand of these,” David said, “shall have charge of the work in the house of the Lord, six thousand shall be officers and judges,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:5",
      "text": "four thousand gatekeepers, and four thousand shall offer praises to the Lord with the instruments which I have made for praise.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:6",
      "text": "And David organized them in divisions corresponding to the sons of Levi: Gershom, Kohath, and Merari.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:7",
      "text": "The sons of Gershom were Ladan and Shime-i.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:8",
      "text": "The sons of Ladan: Jehiel the chief, and Zetham, and Joel, three.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:9",
      "text": "The sons of Shime-i: Shelomoth, Hazi-el, and Haran, three. These were the heads of the fathers' houses of Ladan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:10",
      "text": "And the sons of Shime-i: Jahath, Zina, and Jeush, and Beriah. These four were the sons of Shime-i.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:11",
      "text": "Jahath was the chief, and Zizah the second; but Jeush and Beriah had not many sons, therefore they became a father's house in one reckoning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:12",
      "text": "The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel, four.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:13",
      "text": "The sons of Amram: Aaron and Moses. Aaron was set apart to consecrate the most holy things, that he and his sons for ever should burn incense before the Lord, and minister to him and pronounce blessings in his name for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:14",
      "text": "But the sons of Moses the man of God were named among the tribe of Levi.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:15",
      "text": "The sons of Moses: Gershom and Eliezer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:16",
      "text": "The sons of Gershom: Shebuel the chief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:17",
      "text": "The sons of Eliezer: Rehabiah the chief; Eliezer had no other sons, but the sons of Rehabiah were very many.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:18",
      "text": "The sons of Izhar: Shelomith the chief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:19",
      "text": "The sons of Hebron: Jeriah the chief, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, and Jekameam the fourth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:20",
      "text": "The sons of Uzziel: Micah the chief and Isshiah the second.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:21",
      "text": "The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. The sons of Mahli: Eleazar and Kish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:22",
      "text": "Eleazar died having no sons, but only daughters; their kinsmen, the sons of Kish, married them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:23",
      "text": "The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jeremoth, three.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:24",
      "text": "These were the sons of Levi by their fathers' houses, the heads of fathers' houses as they were registered according to the number of the names of the individuals from twenty years old and upward who were to do the work for the service of the house of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:25",
      "text": "For David said, “The Lord, the God of Israel, has given peace to his people; and he dwells in Jerusalem for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:26",
      "text": "And so the Levites no longer need to carry the tabernacle or any of the things for its service” —",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:27",
      "text": "for by the last words of David these were the number of the Levites from twenty years old and upward—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:28",
      "text": "“but their duty shall be to assist the sons of Aaron for the service of the house of the Lord, having the care of the courts and the chambers, the cleansing of all that is holy, and any work for the service of the house of God;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:29",
      "text": "to assist also with the showbread, the flour for the cereal offering, the wafers of unleavened bread, the baked offering, the offering mixed with oil, and all measures of quantity or size.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:30",
      "text": "And they shall stand every morning, thanking and praising the Lord, and likewise at evening,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:31",
      "text": "and whenever burnt offerings are offered to the Lord on sabbaths, new moons, and feast days, according to the number required of them, continually before the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.23.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 23:32",
      "text": "Thus they shall keep charge of the tent of meeting and the sanctuary, and shall attend the sons of Aaron, their brethren, for the service of the house of the Lord.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
